President Trump visited St. Andrew Catholic School in Orlando, Florida and praised the school for its dedication to providing a full education that enriches both the mind and the soul. He also thanked the principal, Latrina Peters-Gipson, for her incredible work and expressed his gratitude to Superintendent Fortier for his fantastic job. The President mentioned that education is the civil rights issue of our time and emphasized his support for school choice programs. He commended Secretary DeVos for her role in leading the charge for education reform and highlighted Denisha Merriweather, a guest at his address to Congress, as an example of the success that can be achieved through education. President Trump also expressed his love for Florida and his appreciation for the state's management by Governor Rick Scott and Senator Marco Rubio.